{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850181962,"sessionID":"ses_28714cdffffeMT17UE7cT7cuXR","part":{"id":"prt_d78eb51200018Q6EmY8wK9qDkQ","messageID":"msg_d78eb426f001HAnp9QSkSCV841","sessionID":"ses_28714cdffffeMT17UE7cT7cuXR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_cf387cd155614c4aa6784e18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/router  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: JWT Configuration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Add JWT config fields to `Config` struct — `JWTEnabled`, `JWTAlgorithm`, `JWTSecret`, `JWTPrivateKeyPath`, `JWTPublicKeyPath`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTAudience`, `JWTExpiration`, `JWTRefreshExpiration`, `JWTClockSkew`, `JWTAllowQueryParam`\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` JWT defaults — algorithm \"HS256\", issuer \"agentcube\", expiry \"1h\", refresh expiry \"24h\", clock skew \"30s\"\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Add JWT dependency to `go.mod` — `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Phase 2: JWT Data Structures\n19: \n20: - [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `JWTConfig` struct with all JWT settings\n21: - [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `Claims` struct embedding `jwt.RegisteredClaims` with custom fields (Roles, TenantID, Namespace)\n22: - [ ] **2.3** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `UserCredentials` struct for login request\n23: - [ ] **2.4** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `LoginResponse` struct for login response\n24: - [ ] **2.5** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `TokenRefreshRequest` struct\n25: - [ ] **2.6** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `UserValidator` interface\n26: - [ ] **2.7** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `UserClaims` struct\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## Phase 3: JWT Errors\n31: \n32: - [ ] **3.1** Define JWT error variables — `ErrMalformedToken`, `ErrInvalidSignature`, `ErrTokenExpired`, `ErrInvalidAudience`, `ErrInvalidIssuer`, `ErrUnauthorized`, `ErrInvalidCredentials`, `ErrInvalidRefreshToken`\n33: - [ ] **3.2** Define JWT error code constants\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Phase 4: JWT Manager - Core\n38: \n39: - [ ] **4.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `JWTManager` struct with config, keys, metrics, userValidator\n40: - [ ] **4.2** Implement `NewJWTManager(config *JWTConfig, validator UserValidator)` — initialize manager and load keys\n41: - [ ] **4.3** Implement key loading for HS256 (symmetric key from config/env)\n42: - [ ] **4.4** Implement key loading for RS256 (load private/public keys from files)\n43: - [ ] **4.5** Write unit test: HS256 key loading from config\n44: - [ ] **4.6** Write unit test: RS256 key loading from files\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## Phase 5: JWT Token Validation\n49: \n50: - [ ] **5.1** Implement `JWTManager.ValidateToken(tokenString string) (*Claims, error)` — parse and validate JWT\n51: - [ ] **5.2** Implement HS256 token validation with secret key\n52: - [ ] **5.3** Implement RS256 token validation with public key\n53: - [ ] **5.4** Handle signature validation errors\n54: - [ ] **5.5** Handle expiration validation with clock skew\n55: - [ ] **5.6** Handle issuer validation\n56: - [ ] **5.7** Handle audience validation\n57: - [ ] **5.8** Write unit test: Validate valid HS256 token\n58: - [ ] **5.9** Write unit test: Validate expired token returns error\n59: - [ ] **5.10** Write unit test: Validate invalid signature returns error\n60: - [ ] **5.11** Write unit test: Validate malformed token returns error\n61: - [ ] **5.12** Write unit test: Validate wrong audience returns error\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## Phase 6: JWT Token Issuance\n66: \n67: - [ ] **6.1** Implement `JWTManager.IssueToken(user *UserClaims) (string, error)` — issue access token\n68: - [ ] **6.2** Implement `JWTManager.IssueRefreshToken(user *UserClaims) (string, error)` — issue refresh token\n69: - [ ] **6.3** Implement HS256 token signing\n70: - [ ] **6.4** Implement RS256 token signing\n71: - [ ] **6.5** Set claims: sub, exp, iat, nbf, iss, roles, tenant_id, namespace\n72: - [ ] **6.6** Write unit test: Issue token with correct claims\n73: - [ ] **6.7** Write unit test: Issue token with configured expiry\n74: - [ ] **6.8** Write unit test: Issue token with configured issuer\n75: - [ ] **6.9** Write unit test: RS256 token issuance\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## Phase 7: JWT Middleware\n80: \n81: - [ ] **7.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go` — `JWTMiddleware` function\n82: - [ ] **7.2** Implement token extraction from Authorization header (Bearer token)\n83: - [ ] **7.3** Implement token extraction from query parameter (when AllowQueryParam is true)\n84: - [ ] **7.4** Implement public path check — skip JWT validation for public endpoints\n85: - [ ] **7.5** Integrate JWT validation into middleware chain\n86: - [ ] **7.6** Store claims in request context\n87: - [ ] **7.7** Store username in request context\n88: - [ ] **7.8** Write unit test: Extract token from Authorization header\n89: - [ ] **7.9** Write unit test: Extract token from query parameter\n90: - [ ] **7.10** Write unit test: Public endpoint bypasses JWT validation\n91: - [ ] **7.11** Write unit test: Protected endpoint rejects missing token\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Phase 8: Login Handler\n96: \n97: - [ ] **8.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_handler.go` — `HandleLogin` function\n98: - [ ] **8.2** Decode and validate UserCredentials from request body\n99: - [ ] **8.3** Call userValidator.Validate() with username/password\n100: - [ ] **8.4** Issue access token and refresh token on success\n101: - [ ] **8.5** Return LoginResponse with token, type, expires_in\n102: - [ ] **8.6** Return 401 on invalid credentials\n103: - [ ] **8.7** Register `/login` endpoint in router\n104: - [ ] **8.8** Write unit test: Login with valid credentials returns token\n105: - [ ] **8.9** Write unit test: Login with invalid credentials returns 401\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ## Phase 9: Refresh Handler\n110: \n111: - [ ] **9.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_handler.go` — `HandleRefresh` function\n112: - [ ] **9.2** Decode TokenRefreshRequest from request body\n113: - [ ] **9.3** Validate refresh token\n114: - [ ] **9.4** Issue new access token\n115: - [ ] **9.5** Return new access token with expires_in\n116: - [ ] **9.6** Return 401 on invalid/expired refresh token\n117: - [ ] **9.7** Register `/refresh` endpoint in router\n118: - [ ] **9.8** Write unit test: Refresh with valid token returns new access token\n119: - [ ] **9.9** Write unit test: Refresh with expired token returns 401\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## Phase 10: Router Integration\n124: \n125: - [ ] **10.1** Update router initialization to create JWTManager when JWTEnabled\n126: - [ ] **10.2** Add JWT middleware to handler chain\n127: - [ ] **10.3** Configure public paths list: `/health/live`, `/health/ready`, `/metrics`, `/login`, `/refresh`\n128: - [ ] **10.4** Add login and refresh endpoints to router\n129: - [ ] **10.5** Write unit test: Router with JWT enabled applies middleware\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## Phase 11: JWT Metrics\n134: \n135: - [ ] **11.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_metrics.go` — `JWTMetrics` struct\n136: - [ ] **11.2** Implement `jwt_validated_total` counter with result label\n137: - [ ] **11.3** Implement `jwt_issued_total` counter\n138: - [ ] **11.4** Implement `jwt_refreshed_total` counter with result label\n139: - [ ] **11.5** Implement `jwt_validation_errors_total` counter with error_type label\n140: - [ ] **11.6** Integrate metrics into JWTManager\n141: - [ ] **11.7** Increment metrics on validation success/failure\n142: - [ ] **11.8** Increment metrics on token issuance\n143: - [ ] **11.9** Increment metrics on token refresh\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## Phase 12: Validation\n148: \n149: - [ ] **12.1** `go build ./pkg/router/...` — successful compilation\n150: - [ ] **12.2** `go test ./pkg/router/... -v` — all unit tests pass\n151: - [ ] **12.3** Test: JWT with default config uses HS256, 1h expiry\n152: - [ ] **12.4** Test: JWT with custom config uses RS256, 24h expiry\n153: - [ ] **12.5** Test: Valid JWT token validates successfully\n154: - [ ] **12.6** Test: Expired JWT token returns 401\n155: - [ ] **12.7** Test: Invalid signature returns 401\n156: - [ ] **12.8** Test: Malformed token returns 400\n157: - [ ] **12.9** Test: Claims extracted and available in context\n158: - [ ] **12.10** Test: Login endpoint issues JWT token\n159: - [ ] **12.11** Test: Token refresh endpoint works\n160: - [ ] **12.12** Test: Public endpoints bypass JWT validation\n161: - [ ] **12.13** Test: JWT metrics are exported\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Dependencies\n166: \n167: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` — JWT token handling\n168: - `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` — Metrics\n169: - AR-010 (completed) — Router Session Management\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## References\n174: \n175: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md`\n176: - Design: `pkg/router/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: JWT Configuration\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Add JWT config fields to `Config` struct — `JWTEnabled`, `JWTAlgorithm`, `JWTSecret`, `JWTPrivateKeyPath`, `JWTPublicKeyPath`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTAudience`, `JWTExpiration`, `JWTRefreshExpiration`, `JWTClockSkew`, `JWTAllowQueryParam`\n- [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` JWT defaults — algorithm \"HS256\", issuer \"agentcube\", expiry \"1h\", refresh expiry \"24h\", clock skew \"30s\"\n- [ ] **1.3** Add JWT dependency to `go.mod` — `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: JWT Data Structures\n\n- [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `JWTConfig` struct with all JWT settings","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775850181936,"end":1775850181960}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850181966,"sessionID":"ses_28714cdffffeMT17UE7cT7cuXR","part":{"id":"prt_d78eb4ce2001I4vKkrBANOA9Jp","messageID":"msg_d78eb426f001HAnp9QSkSCV841","sessionID":"ses_28714cdffffeMT17UE7cT7cuXR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9713b0ea56754a29b2ac4e04","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing JWT authentication and token issuance in `pkg/router`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-011\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/router`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The router module requires JWT-based authentication to secure API endpoints and enable token-based access control. This includes both JWT validation for incoming requests and token issuance for authenticated clients.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirement: JWT Configuration\n23: \n24: ### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with default configuration\n25: \n26: **GIVEN** a Router instance is created with `jwtEnabled: true` and no explicit JWT configuration\n27: **WHEN** the router initializes\n28: **THEN** it SHOULD use default values: secret from environment or config, algorithm \"HS256\", expiry \"1h\"\n29: \n30: ### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with custom configuration\n31: \n32: **GIVEN** a Router instance with JWT configuration: `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"`, `jwtExpiry: \"24h\"`, `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n33: **WHEN** the router initializes\n34: **THEN** it SHOULD configure RS256 algorithm, 24 hour expiry, and issuer to \"agentcube\"\n35: \n36: ### Scenario: Router disables JWT authentication\n37: \n38: **GIVEN** a Router instance with `jwtEnabled: false` (default)\n39: **WHEN** HTTP requests are received\n40: **THEN** the router SHOULD NOT validate JWT tokens\n41: **AND** no JWT middleware SHOULD be applied\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n46: \n47: ### Scenario: Router validates valid JWT token\n48: \n49: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and configured secret\n50: **WHEN** a request arrives with a valid JWT token in Authorization header \"Bearer <valid-token>\"\n51: **THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n52: **AND** extract the claims into the request context\n53: \n54: ### Scenario: Router rejects expired JWT token\n55: \n56: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n57: **WHEN** a request arrives with an expired JWT token\n58: **THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n59: **AND** return 401 Unauthorized with appropriate error message\n60: \n61: ### Scenario: Router rejects invalid signature JWT token\n62: \n63: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n64: **WHEN** a request arrives with a JWT token that has invalid signature\n65: **THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n66: **AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid signature\" error\n67: \n68: ### Scenario: Router rejects malformed JWT token\n69: \n70: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n71: **WHEN** a request arrives with a malformed JWT token (not 3 parts)\n72: **THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n73: **AND** return 400 Bad Request with \"malformed token\" error\n74: \n75: ### Scenario: Router extracts claims from valid JWT\n76: \n77: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n78: **WHEN** a request arrives with valid JWT containing claims: `sub`, `exp`, `roles`\n79: **THEN** the claims SHOULD be available in request context\n80: **AND** can be accessed by downstream handlers\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## Requirement: JWT Token Issuance\n85: \n86: ### Scenario: Router issues JWT token for valid credentials\n87: \n88: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint configured\n89: **WHEN** a POST request arrives with valid username and password\n90: **THEN** the router SHOULD authenticate the credentials\n91: **AND** issue a JWT token with user claims\n92: **AND** return the token in the response\n93: \n94: ### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured expiry\n95: \n96: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtExpiry: \"2h\"`\n97: **WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n98: **THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `exp` claim set to current time + 2 hours\n99: \n100: ### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured issuer\n101: \n102: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n103: **WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n104: **THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `iss` claim set to \"agentcube\"\n105: \n106: ### Scenario: Router rejects invalid credentials\n107: \n108: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint\n109: **WHEN** a POST request arrives with invalid username or password\n110: **THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n111: **AND** NOT issue a JWT token\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ## Requirement: JWT Middleware\n116: \n117: ### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from Authorization header\n118: \n119: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n120: **WHEN** a request arrives with header `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n121: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token\n122: **AND** validate it\n123: \n124: ### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from query parameter\n125: \n126: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware configured to allow query param\n127: **WHEN** a request arrives with query param `?token=<token>`\n128: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token from query\n129: **AND** validate it\n130: \n131: ### Scenario: JWT middleware allows public endpoints\n132: \n133: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n134: **WHEN** a request arrives at a public endpoint (e.g., `/health`, `/login`)\n135: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD skip JWT validation\n136: **AND** allow the request through\n137: \n138: ### Scenario: JWT middleware blocks unauthorized access\n139: \n140: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n141: **WHEN** a request arrives at a protected endpoint without token\n142: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Requirement: JWT Claims\n147: \n148: ### Scenario: Router includes user ID in JWT claims\n149: \n150: **GIVEN** a user logs in successfully\n151: **WHEN** JWT token is issued\n152: **THEN** the token SHOULD include `sub` claim with user identifier\n153: \n154: ### Scenario: Router includes roles in JWT claims\n155: \n156: **GIVEN** a user with roles \"admin\", \"user\" logs in\n157: **WHEN** JWT token is issued\n158: **THEN** the token SHOULD include `roles` claim with array [\"admin\", \"user\"]\n159: \n160: ### Scenario: Router includes custom claims in JWT\n161: \n162: **GIVEN** a Router configured with custom claims (e.g., `tenant_id`)\n163: **WHEN** JWT token is issued\n164: **THEN** the token SHOULD include the custom claims\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Requirement: Token Refresh\n169: \n170: ### Scenario: Router supports token refresh endpoint\n171: \n172: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and refresh endpoint configured\n173: **WHEN** a valid (non-expired) JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n174: **THEN** a new JWT token SHOULD be issued\n175: **AND** the new token SHOULD have fresh expiry time\n176: \n177: ### Scenario: Router rejects refresh with expired token\n178: \n179: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT refresh enabled\n180: **WHEN** an expired JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n181: **THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Requirement: Key Management\n186: \n187: ### Scenario: Router loads JWT secret from configuration\n188: \n189: **GIVEN** a Router with `jwtSecret: \"my-secret-key\"` configured\n190: **WHEN** JWT validation or issuance occurs\n191: **THEN** the router SHOULD use \"my-secret-key\" for signing/verification\n192: \n193: ### Scenario: Router supports RS256 with private key\n194: \n195: **GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and private key configured\n196: **WHEN** JWT token is issued\n197: **THEN** the token SHOULD be signed with RS256 using the private key\n198: \n199: ### Scenario: Router validates RS256 token with public key\n200: \n201: **GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and public key configured\n202: **WHEN** a request arrives with RS256-signed JWT\n203: **THEN** the router SHOULD validate using the public key\n204: \n205: ### Scenario: Router validates audience claim\n206: \n207: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n208: **WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"agentcube-api\"`\n209: **THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n210: \n211: ### Scenario: Router rejects token with wrong audience\n212: \n213: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n214: **WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"other-api\"`\n215: **THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n216: **AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid audience\" error\n217: \n218: ### Scenario: Router handles clock skew\n219: \n220: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and clock skew tolerance configured\n221: **WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that expires within the clock skew window\n222: **THEN** the router SHOULD accept the token as valid\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ## Requirement: JWT Metrics\n227: \n228: ### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation success\n229: \n230: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n231: **WHEN** a valid JWT is successfully validated\n232: **THEN** the metric `jwt_validated_total` SHOULD be incremented with label `result=\"success\"`\n233: \n234: ### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation failure\n235: \n236: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n237: **WHEN** a JWT validation fails (expired, invalid signature, etc.)\n238: **THEN** the metric `jwt_validation_errors_total` SHOULD be incremented\n239: **AND** include error type label\n240: \n241: ### Scenario: Router tracks JWT token issuance\n242: \n243: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n244: **WHEN** a JWT token is successfully issued\n245: **THEN** the metric `jwt_issued_total` SHOULD be incremented\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## Acceptance Criteria\n250: \n251: - [ ] JWT tokens are validated on protected endpoints\n252: - [ ] Expired tokens are rejected with 401\n253: - [ ] Invalid signatures are rejected with 401\n254: - [ ] Valid tokens expose claims in request context\n255: - [ ] Login endpoint issues JWT tokens\n256: - [ ] Token expiry is configurable\n257: - [ ] Token issuer is configurable\n258: - [ ] JWT algorithm is configurable (HS256, RS256)\n259: - [ ] Public endpoints bypass JWT validation\n260: - [ ] Token refresh endpoint works correctly\n261: - [ ] Custom claims can be included in tokens\n262: - [ ] Invalid credentials are rejected\n263: - [ ] Audience claim is validated when configured\n264: - [ ] Clock skew is handled gracefully\n265: - [ ] JWT metrics are exported (jwt_validated_total, jwt_issued_total, jwt_validation_errors_total)\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ## References\n270: \n271: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md`\n272: - Proposal: `proposal.md`\n\n(End of file - total 272 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing JWT authentication and token issuance in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-011\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module requires JWT-based authentication to secure API endpoints and enable token-based access control. This includes both JWT validation for incoming requests and token issuance for authenticated clients.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775850181933,"end":1775850181963}}}}
